# Adversary fixture: FM2 — @type: @id coerces string value to IRI
# Failure mode: implementations that treat the string value "ex:bob" as a
#   plain literal when the term has @type: @id in its definition, rather than
#   expanding it to the full IRI http://example.org/bob.
# JSON-LD 1.1 §5.3.2 (Value Expansion): when a term's type mapping is @id,
#   a string value is expanded as an IRI reference, not as a plain literal.
# The object must be the IRI <http://example.org/bob>, not the literal "ex:bob".
# spec-ref: W3C JSON-LD 1.1 §5.3.2 Value Expansion, §6.4 Expansion algorithm
# divergence-hypothesis: ObjectMismatch — lax parsers emit literal "ex:bob";
#   conformant parsers emit IRI <http://example.org/bob>.
outcome: accept
fact-count: 1
ACCEPT
<http://example.org/alice> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/knows> <http://example.org/bob> .
